properties.areaDesc: Coastal waters from Cape Henlopen to Fenwick Island DE out 20 nm; Coastal waters from Cape May NJ to Cape Henlopen DE out 20 nm
properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued February 8 at 12:40AM EST until February 8 at 10:00AM EST by NWS Mount Holly NJ
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Low Water Advisory, abnormally low water levels.
For the Small Craft Advisory, west winds 15 to 25 knots with
gusts up to 30 knots and seas 4 to 7 feet.

* WHERE...The coastal waters from Cape May, New Jersey to Fenwick
Island, Delaware.

* WHEN...For the Low Water Advisory, until 5:00 AM. For the Small
Craft Advisory, until 10:00 AM this morning.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft. Below
normal water levels will result in hazardous navigating
conditions.
properties.instruction:
Inexperienced mariners, especially those operating a small
vessel, should avoid navigating in hazardous conditions.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 AM EST THIS MORNING... ...LOW WATER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 5 AM EST EARLY THIS MORNING... ...GALE WARNING IS CANCELLED
